##<a id='using'></a> VMware Tanzu Kubernetes Grid Integrated(TKGI) Support

The Qualys Cloud Agent tile is supported on TKGI as well, formerly known as Pivotal Container Service (PKS). For more information about VMware Tanzu Kubernetes Grid, visit the [VMware Tanzu Kubernetes Grid](https://tanzu.vmware.com/kubernetes-grid) page.

###<a id='installation'></a> Installation

The Qualys Cloud Agent for VMware Tanzu tile includes support for VMware Tanzu Kubernetes Grid Integrated edition. See the [Installing and Configuring Qualys Cloud Agent for VMware Tanzu](https://docs.pivotal.io/partners/qualys-cloud-agent/installing.html) for guidance on how to install the Qualys Cloud Agent tile.

After the tile is installed with VMware Tanzu Kubernetes Grid, Qualysâ€™ Cloud Agent will be automatically deployed on all Kubernetes clusters created by the VMware Tanzu Kubernetes Grid Service Broker. 

###<a id='configuration'></a> Configuration

Agent configurations specified to the tile will apply for agents running on BOSH as well as on Kubernetes; see the [Installing and Configuring Qualys Cloud Agent for VMware Tanzu](https://docs.pivotal.io/partners/qualys-cloud-agent/installing.html) page for an overview of which configurations can be set for deploying Qualys Cloud Agent.

##<a id='upgrading'></a> Upgrading Tile

To upgrade the Qualys Cloud Agent for VMware Tanzu, select upgraded product from the list and click **Apply Changes**. Confirm and click **Review Pending Changes**.

<img src="images/update_tile.png" alt="Upgrading Tile">

Click **Apply Changes** to complete the upgradation process.


##<a id='deletion'></a> Uninstalling Tile

To uninstall the Qualys Cloud Agent for VMware Tanzu, click **delete** icon from that tile.  Confirm and click **Review Pending Changes**.

<img src="images/deletion.png" alt="Uninstalling Tile">

Click **Apply Changes** to complete the uninstallation process.
